description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for suitable individuals to take up the post of substantive whole time Consultant in ENT within this well-established progressive and friendly Department of Ear Nose and Throat Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from individuals with an interest in Otology would be particularly welcome although other applicants would also be of interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Royal Hospital is a long established and financially stable Foundation Trust serving a population of around 400,000 patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has good links with tertiary centres to the North in Sheffield and to the south in Derby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cancer services are provided as part of the South Yorkshire Cancer Alliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will join a number of established ENT Consultant colleagues in delivering an ENT service to the Trust and population of North Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individuals are sought who have the ability, enthusiasm and interest to participate with existing Consultant colleagues in further developing the ENT service while providing sub-speciality input within their area of interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full GMC registration and completion of Specialist Training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Royal Hospital is a successful Foundation Trust, providing acute services in all the major specialties for Chesterfield and the surrounding rural areas of North Derbyshire. The Trust has an excellent friendly atmosphere making it popular with trainee medical staff from both Sheffield and Nottingham. The Town of Chesterfield is located close to the Peak District National Park as well as being close to the cities of Sheffield and Nottingham. There are excellent direct rail links to London and other major cities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
